OL,3,CMothers whose daughters were killed by
OL,4,Cpartners campaign for harsher sentences
OL,6,FWomen murdered by strangers in
OL,7,Funprovoked attacks. They shatter
OL,8,Ffamilies, make us all shudder and
OL,9,Foccasionally they prompt politicians
OL,10,Fto act.
OL,12,FBut statistically such attacks,
OL,13,Fmercifully, are relatively rare.
OL,15,FExtreme male violence against women is
OL,16,Fmuch more likely to happen in the
OL,17,Fplace they should feel safest: their
OL,18,Fown homes. And the perpetrators are
OL,19,Flikely to be a current or former
OL,20,Fpartner.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G2/16
