OL,3,CMothers whose daughters were killed by
OL,4,Cpartners campaign for harsher sentences
OL,6,FI meet three mothers united in the
OL,7,Fworst possible circumstances. As we
OL,8,Fgather in a kitchen around cups of
OL,9,Ftea, Elaine Newborough, Julie Devey
OL,10,Fand Carole Gould tell me about their
OL,11,Fbeautiful young daughters: Megan,
OL,12,FPoppy and Ellie. Daughters with
OL,13,Feverything to live for, until each was
OL,14,Fmurdered by their partners or ex-
OL,15,Fpartners in the most savage knife
OL,16,Fattacks imaginable. Ellie was just 17.
OL,18,FAll thought their grief and trauma
OL,19,Fcould not get any worse.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G6/16
