OL,3,CMothers whose daughters were killed by
OL,4,Cpartners campaign for harsher sentences
OL,6,FIt hinges largely on a change made by
OL,7,Fthe Labour government in 2010. Just
OL,8,Flike now - there was a public outcry
OL,9,Fover knife crime, in particular in the
OL,10,Fwake of the murder of 16-year-old Ben
OL,11,FKinsella, stabbed to death in the
OL,12,Fstreet by three men.
OL,14,FIt led to a decision to raise the
OL,15,Fsentencing level for murder with a
OL,16,Fknife taken to a scene with intent -
OL,17,Fto a minimum tariff of 25 years.
OL,19,FIt made such murders in effect
OL,20,F'special cases' - along with gun crime
OL,21,Fand terrorism.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G9/16
