OL,3,CMothers whose daughters were killed by
OL,4,Cpartners campaign for harsher sentences
OL,6,Fis joined by ITV's Tonight programme
OL,7,Fproducer, Anna Manton and the Chair of
OL,8,Fcharity Refuge, Hetti Barkworth-Nanton
OL,9,Fto talk about domestic violence
OL,10,Fmurderers get shorter sentences
OL,12,FSo called 'domestic' murders - where
OL,13,Fthe weapon, usually a kitchen knife,
OL,14,Fis already in the home - remained at
OL,15,Fthe minimum tariff of 15 years.
OL,17,FBut campaigners - not least the three
OL,18,Fmothers of Poppy, Carole and Ellie -
OL,19,Fsay that means their daughters'
OL,20,Fmurders are not treated with equal
OL,21,Fgravity.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G    G10/16
