OL,3,CMothers whose daughters were killed by
OL,4,Cpartners campaign for harsher sentences
OL,6,FTheir pressure prompted the government
OL,7,Fto act.
OL,9,FIt commissioned a review of domestic
OL,10,Fhomicide by leading barrister Clare
OL,11,FWade KC, which was published last
OL,12,Fyear. Some of the recommendations she
OL,13,Fmade have already been taken up by the
OL,14,Fgovernment which are already leading
OL,15,Fto longer sentencing.
OL,17,FBut crucially - and controversially -
OL,18,FClare Wade did not recommend raising
OL,19,Fthe minimum tariff for domestic
OL,20,Fhomicide from 15 years to 25.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G    G11/16
