OL,3,CMothers whose daughters were killed by
OL,4,Cpartners campaign for harsher sentences
OL,6,FOthers, like the chair of Refuge,
OL,7,FHetti Barkworth-Nanton, says this
OL,8,Fpotential anomaly could, however,
OL,9,Feasily be addressed by the legal
OL,10,Fsystem to offer protection to such
OL,11,Fwomen.
OL,13,FThere are other complexities too which
OL,14,Fmake this a far less straightforward
OL,15,Fchange that one might imagine.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G    G13/16
