OL,3,CMothers whose daughters were killed by
OL,4,Cpartners campaign for harsher sentences
OL,6,FBut for the mothers of Poppy, Ellie
OL,7,Fand Megan it is a simple question of
OL,8,Ffairness and equality before the law -
OL,9,Fa recognition that their daughters'
OL,10,Fmurders are as grave as if they had
OL,11,Fhappened in the street at the hands of
OL,12,Fa stranger.
OL,14,FThere is a window of opportunity for
OL,15,Feveryone to have their say... and it
OL,16,Fcloses in ten days' time.
OL,18,FIn that time it is likely,
OL,19,Fstatistically, that two more women
OL,20,Fwill have lost their lives in a
OL,21,Fvicious domestic attack.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G    G14/16
